---
title: One-Pot Vegan Coconut Curry Soup with Chickpeas, Cauliflower & Toast
description: Northern Indian flavors take center stage in this lush, savory-sweet and spicy soup. Here, aromatic onion, garam masala, curry, and tomato paste are cooked just until fragrant. Next, cauliflower and chickpeas are added to create another layer of dimension—all simmered in coconut milk and savory vegetable stock. Scallion greens are sprinkled over top for a pop of freshness. Toasted ciabatta adds a crisp crunch on the side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vegan-tomato-coconut-curry-soup-75f671e6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-vegan-coconut-curry-soup-6317a0d36f2cec7af7043c50-1ffc4f22.pdf
cuisine: Indian
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1880 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-vegan-coconut-curry-soup-6317a0d36f2cec7af7043c50
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(diced). Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or
grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Cut @cauliflower florets{10%oz} into bite-size
pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} (use a #large pot{} for
4 servings) over medium heat. Add onion and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add
scallion whites and garlic; cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

> Add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Add another drizzle of oil. Stir in @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @cumin{1%tsp},
@tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and half the @garam masala{1%tsp} (use all for 4) until
combined. Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1} in #container{} before opening.

To pot with veggies, add coconut milk, cauliflower, @chickpeas{1} and their
liquid, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a
big pinch of @salt{} (we used 1 tsp; 2 tsp for 4). Stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer, then cover and reduce heat to medium low. Cook until
cauliflower is almost tender, ~{6%minutes}. Uncover and cook until soup has
thickened, ~{5-7%minutes} more.

> If your soup isn't thick enough, simmer until it reaches desired consistency.
> If your soup is too thick, add a few splashes of water.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, halve @ciabatta bread{1}. Drizzle cut sides with @olive oil{1%tsp} and
sprinkle with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast until golden, then cut in half on a
diagonal.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with toast
on the side.
